	<h2>Our programme</h2>

	<p>Our programme is appropriate for children learning to read with Systematic Synthetic Phonics in Reception and Year 1.  It follows closely the curriculum laid out by Letters and Sounds, but can be customized by your teachers to fit whichever curriculum you follow.  It also includes our own phonics reading scheme with over 40 stories written by Roald Dahl’s grandson, Luke Kelly.  All our stories and games use our Phonics Reading Pad, designed to help learners strengthen their knowledge of the relationship between letters and their sounds.</p>  

